ro &#8211; Fixing Geo Location!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com\">AdRotate Plugin for WordPress</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Arnan de Gans\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1385:\"<p>If you use Geo Location and have already updated to 3.8.12 you should update to 3.8.13 as soon as possible.<br />\nA bug introduced in 3.8.12 may cause AdRotate Pro to stop getting data from Freegeoip. So the Geo Location feature doesn&#8217;t work for some users.<br />\nThis update resolves this issue. You may have to resave a group for the fix to take effect.</p>\n<p>On top of that, based on some user feedback I&#8217;ve reworked the Schedule filter so it uses less MySQL queries. Reducing server load.</p>\n<h3>Changelog:</h3>\n<div class=\"shortcode-unorderedlist arrow\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Reduced MySQL load for some ads</li>\n<li>[fix] Geo Location not fetching data for some users</li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n\n<p><strong>Update:</strong> There is another bug caused by the patch. Some users are affected by this when using Geo Location. A patch is being tested right now (1:15pm CET) and should be ready later today.</p>\n<p><strong>Update 2:</strong> The error has been patched and a fixed version of version 3.8.13 has been uploaded.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2013/10/adrotate-pro-fixing-geo-location/\">AdRotate Pro &#8211; Fixing Geo Location!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com\">AdRotate Plugin for WordPress</a>.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/6E_UFKOqECE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs